LEEN BRIDGE‚ 222 sqq. This was the bridge over the low lying meadowg connecting Fishergate with the great bridge over the Trent (Hethbeth Bridge). The Leen Bridge was also known as the Town Bridge or the Bridge of Nottingham. It consisted of twenty arches, and is now represented by the Flood Road (London Road). This Bridge is shown in most of the old views of the town.
